        planning and employee training.

6. Planned changes to improve safety.

Safety improvement is an on-going process at the facility. Periodic evaluations are performed to assess the maintenance of safe conditions. The facility has been evaluated for improvements to meet the current ANSI Code K-61.1, 1999 and these improvements will be made in the near future.
